---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import NewsletterSignup from '../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About GhanaScope: Who We Are and Why We Exist"
  description="GhanaScope provides honest, evidence-grounded Ghana business intelligence for diaspora investors and founders. Built by Richmond Owusu Duah."
  keywords="about GhanaScope, Ghana business intelligence, Richmond Owusu Duah, diaspora investment platform"
>
  <div class="hero hero--bg hero--about">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-label">Our Mission</div>
      <h1>About GhanaScope</h1>
      <p>Honest intelligence for real decisions</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-content">
      <div class="section reveal">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="section-title">Why GhanaScope Exists</div>
        </div>

        <div class="article-body">
          <p>Every diaspora investor considering Ghana faces the same problem: <strong>nobody tells you what actually fails.</strong></p>

          <p>Consultants sell optimism. Government agencies market opportunity. LinkedIn is full of "Ghana is rising" posts. But when you send $30,000 to start a business, nobody warned you about:</p>

          <ul>
            <li>The GIPC capital requirement that locks you out of formal registration</li>
            <li>The local partner who disappears with your investment</li>
            <li>The infrastructure gap that doubles your operating costs</li>
            <li>The policy change that invalidates your business model overnight</li>
            <li>The cedi depreciation that erases your margins</li>
          </ul>

          <p>GhanaScope was built to fix this. We provide <strong>honest, evidence-grounded, continuously updated</strong> intelligence on Ghana's business environment. We tell you what works, what fails, and why, with data, not optimism.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section reveal">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="section-title">How We Work</div>
        </div>

        <div class="article-body">
          <p>GhanaScope is powered by <strong>GhanaWorld</strong>, a multi-agent intelligence system that has run 40+ analytical cycles across Ghana's economy. Each cycle:</p>

          <ul>
            <li>Ingests fresh economic data (GDP, inflation, exchange rates, policy changes)</li>
            <li>Runs sector analysis across agriculture, fintech, real estate, manufacturing, and more</li>
            <li>Scores opportunities with weighted criteria (market size, infrastructure viability, execution feasibility, currency risk, diaspora fit)</li>
            <li>Identifies failure patterns and risk cascades</li>
            <li>Tracks known unknowns: the questions we cannot yet answer</li>
          </ul>

          <p>Every analysis goes through an enforcement process that checks for hallucination, unsupported optimism, omitted risks, and false completeness. If we do not have the data, we say so. If the picture is unclear, we say so.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section reveal">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="section-title">Who This Is For</div>
        </div>

        <div class="card-grid cols-2">
          <div class="grid-card">
            <h3>Diaspora Founders</h3>
            <p>Considering starting a business in Ghana. Need honest risk assessment, execution barriers, and remote-viability analysis.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid-card">
            <h3>Diaspora Investors</h3>
            <p>Evaluating Ghana-based opportunities from abroad. Need structured data, scenario models, and stated confidence levels.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid-card">
            <h3>Institutional Analysts</h3>
            <p>DFIs, PE/VC, research teams assessing Ghana's sectors. Need sector intelligence with evidence grounding.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid-card">
            <h3>Policy Professionals</h3>
            <p>Tracking Ghana's regulatory and macroeconomic environment. Need impact analysis, not press release summaries.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section reveal">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="section-title">Built By</div>
        </div>

        <div class="article-body">
          <p><strong>Richmond Owusu Duah</strong>, software engineer and builder focused on Ghana's economic intelligence infrastructure. Based in the diaspora. Building tools that make real information accessible to real people making real decisions.</p>

          <p>Contact: <a href="https://github.com/Rowusuduah">GitHub</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="data-box" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
          <h4>Our Principles</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>No hallucinated data.</strong> Every claim is traceable to a source.</li>
            <li><strong>No suppressed risk.</strong> Every opportunity analysis includes what kills it.</li>
            <li><strong>No false completeness.</strong> If we do not know, we say so.</li>
            <li><strong>No generic Africa frameworks.</strong> Every analysis is Ghana-specific.</li>
            <li><strong>No political endorsement.</strong> Analysis is structural, not partisan.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <NewsletterSignup />
</Base>

<style>
  .about-content {
    max-width: 720px;
  }
</style>
